  "text": "Recent years, there have been many learning-based image compression approaches showing excellent performance and some methods [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] even perform better than JPEG, JPEG2000 and BPG (a state of the art lossy coding method). Besides, due to its neural network structure and characteristic of backpropagation, a learning-based approach is possible to be combined with another face recognition network and trained jointly. Inspired by [CITATION_3] , in this paper, we replace the conventional codec in Fig. 1 with a compressionreconstruction network in the form of autoencoder combined with a standard lossless image codec PNG. Aiming at improving the accuracy of face recognition, the compressionreconstruction network and face recognition network are trained as a whole. Finally, a higher verification accuracy was obtained on the LFW dataset compressed by our jointly optimized compression network than on the LFW dataset compressed by JPEG and JPEG2000.",
